==Subsidiaries==
[[Cassa di Risparmio di Loreto]], Medioleasing and Focus Gestioni SGR were subsidiaries of the group as at 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bancamarche.it/chi_siamo|title=Chi siamo|trans-title=About us|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140417091029/http://www.bancamarche.it/chi_siamo|archivedate=17 April 2014|publisher=Banca delle Marche|language=Italian}}</ref> Mediocredito Fondiario Centroitalia, which was absorbed into Banca delle Marche in 2003,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.bancamarche.it/ComunicatoStampa.aspx?id=21|title=Fusione Per Incorporazione Con Mediocredito E Carilo|date=6 November 2002|access-date=21 April 2016|publisher=Banca delle Marche|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bancamarche.it/download/BdM_Bilancio_2003_corr.zip|title=2003 Financial Statement and Reports|date=11 November 2004|access-date=10 March 2016|publisher=Banca delle Marche}}</ref> was a merger of Mediocredito delle Marche and Istituto di Credito Fondiario delle Marche, Umbria, Abruzzo e Molise in 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzettaufficiale.it/eli/id/1992/07/16/092A3363/sg|title=Approvazione del progetto di ristrutturazione presentato dal Mediocredito delle Marche, Istituto di credito fondiario delle Marche, Umbria, Abruzzo e Molise|date=16 July 1992|access-date=10 March 2016|publisher=Italian Republic Official Gazette|author=Ministry of the Treasury|language=Italian}}</ref>

The bank also formed a joint venture company in [[bancassurance]] with [[CGU plc]] (via subsidiary now known as [[Aviva Italia Holding]]) in 1999.<ref>[http://ec.europa.eu/competition/mergers/cases/decisions/m1627_en.pdf Case No IV/M.1627 : CU Italia / Banca delle Marche / JV]</ref>

==Sponsorship==
The bank was a sponsor of sports team [[Associazione Sportiva Volley Lube]] and [[Fabriano Basket]]; the venue [[PalaRossini]] was named after the bank.

